Class TabularPropertyInspector

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.awt.Component
      • java.awt.Container
        • javax.swing.JComponent
          • javax.swing.JPanel
            • com.developmentontheedge.beans.swing.TabularPropertyInspector
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    AbstractPropertyInspector, Transactable, ImageObserver, MenuContainer, Serializable, Accessible
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    PagedTabularPropertyInspector

    public class TabularPropertyInspector
extends JPanel
implements AbstractPropertyInspector, Transactable
    This property inspector display several beans of same kind in tabular view (like JTable).
    See Also:
    Serialized Form

      • explore

        public void explore(RowModel rowModel,
                    ColumnModel columnModel)
        Main "entry point" for TabularPropertyInspector. It is used to supply list of beans to be shown in the tabular form along with model describeing what columns must be shown.
        Parameters:
        rowModel - the model to retrieve the list of beans to be dispayed
        columnModel - the model describing columns to be shown

      • registerListeners

      • explore

        public void explore(RowModel rowModel,
                    Object templateBean,
                    int showMode)
        Main "entry point" for TabularPropertyInspector. It is used to supply list of beans to be shown in the tabular form along with template bean used to retrieve list of columns to be shown.
        Parameters:
        rowModel - the model to retrieve the list of beans to be dispayed
        templateBean - the properties of the templateBean will be used to calculate the list of columns to show
        showMode - Should be combination of SHOW_USUAL, SHOW_EXPERT, SHOW_HIDDEN, SHOW_PREFERRED

      • explore

        public void explore(Object[] beans)
        Main "entry point" for TabularPropertyInspector. It supplies the list of beans to be shown in the form of array. Columns to be shown are calculated using properties of the first bean in the array

      • explore

        public void explore(Iterator beans)
        Main "entry point" for TabularPropertyInspector. It supplies the list of beans to be shown in the form of iterator. This method is intended for huge lists of beans like results of SQL queries Columns to be shown are calculated using properties of the first bean return by iterator
